{{Infobox institute |name = Canadian Society for Continental Philosophy |image = |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |founder = [[Gary Madison]], [[Anthony Kerby]], John van Buren, John King, Michael Yeo and [[Jeff Mitscherling]] |established = 1984 |mission = the study of [[continental philosophy]] |focus = |president = [[Scott Marratto]] |chairman = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |adjunct_faculty = |staff = |key_people = |budget = |endowment = |debt = |num_members = |subsidiaries = |owner = |non-profit_slogan = |former_name = |location = |coor = |address = |website = [https://www.c-scp.org/ c-scp.org] |footnotes = }}
'''Canadian Society for Continental Philosophy (CSCP)''' is an organization whose purpose is to pursue and exchange philosophical ideas inspired by [[Continental European tradition]]s. It was established in 1984 under the name '''Canadian Society for Hermeneutics and Postmodern Thought''' and its name changed in 2004. CSCP also publishes ''[[Symposium: Canadian Journal of Continental Philosophy]]'' and holds an annual meeting in Canada each fall.<ref>{{cite web|title=CFP: Canadian Society for Continental Philosophy {{!}}|url=http://www.spep.org/papers/cfp-canadian-society-for-continental-philosophy/|website=[[Society for Phenomenology and Existential Philosophy]]|accessdate=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2015 Conference of the Canadian Society for Continental Philosophy|url=https://www.concordia.ca/cuevents/main/2015/10/29/conference-of-the-canadian-society-of-continental-philosophy.html|website=www.concordia.ca|accessdate=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Society for Continental Philosophy: All Thoughts are Equal — University of Minnesota Press|url=https://www.upress.umn.edu/press/press-clips/canadian-society-for-continental-philosophy-all-thoughts-are-equal|website=www.upress.umn.edu|accessdate=3 January 2018|language=en}}</ref>
