{{Infobox book | name = System of Transcendental Idealism | title_orig = System des transcendentalen<!--[sic]--> Idealismus | translator = | image = File:System des transcendentalen Idealismus.png | caption = | author = [[Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph Schelling]] | country = Germany | language = German | subject = [[Philosophy]] | published = 1800 | pages = | isbn= |dewey= |congress= |oclc= | notes = }} '''''System of Transcendental Idealism''''' ({{lang-de|System des transcendentalen<!--[sic]--> Idealismus}}) is a book by [[Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph Schelling]] published in 1800. It has been called Schelling's most important work.<ref name="rockmore">[[Tom Rockmore]], ''Kant and Idealism'', [[Yale University Press]], 2007, p. 72.</ref> In this work, Schelling attempted a [[Immanuel Kant|Kant]]ian project to discover the ground of knowledge.<ref name="rockmore"></ref>
